article.headline: Liberty 57, Winthrop 47
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Seth Curry scored 16 points to lead Liberty to a 57-47 win over Winthrop on Saturday night. Kyle Ohman added 11 points for the Flames (17-8, 8-5 Big South Conference), who won for the seventh time in their last nine games. Curry, who came into the game averaging 20.4 points per contest, hit just 5 of 14 from the field. He went 4-for-4 from the foul line. Charles Corbin led the Eagles (6-17, 5-8) with 12 points and Chris Malcolm had 10. The Flames led by two points at halftime, but Liberty went on a 15-2 run during a five-minute span midway through the second to seal the win. Liberty didn't shoot very well in the game -- 40.8 percent (20 of 49) -- but Winthrop was even worse, going 18 for 54 from the floor (33.3 percent). The Eagles have lost four straight games.
